      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SUPER SEAFARER (1) is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by 3 lengths at Warrnambool in a handy 22.36 beating Paw Nickara. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. One of the key runners again. GUITAR TANGO (2) produced a moderate run last time when fifth at this track over 410m behind Cliff The Boss (23.85) in a Grade 5. Form from his last run is proving strong. Deserves plenty of respect. CAUSING RUBBLE (3) doesn't win out of turn but looks close to breaking through. Has been in the minors the last two runs, the latest finishing third (22.76) at Geelong. Expected to feature. BUNDY PARADISE (7) cannot be dismissed although new to this venue.",
